<h5 class='border-bottom my-3 py-3'><em class="bi bi-gear-wide-connected"></em> JSON API</h5>

<p><%= _('This API allows you to interface with Password Pusher via JSON.  This can be utilized by existing utilities such as curl, wget or any programming language.  See the examples below for some ideas.') %></p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="/api"><%= _('API Endpoint Documentation') %></a></li>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/pglombardo/PasswordPusher/wiki/Password-API"><%= _('Walkthrough & Examples') %></a></li>
</ul>

<h5 class='border-bottom my-3 py-3'><em class="bi bi-speedometer"></em> <%= _('Examples') %></h5>

<h6 class='border-bottom my-3 py-3'>Curl</h6>

<pre class="border p-3"><code>curl -X POST --data "password[payload]=mypassword&amp;password[expire_after_days]=2&amp;password[expire_after_views]=10" https://pwpush.com/p.json
</code></pre>

<h6 class='border-bottom my-3 py-3'>Browser Dev Console</h6>

<p><%= _('You can test this in your browser Javascript console by going to the front page of Password Pusher and enter:') %></p>

<pre class="border p-3"><code> $.post('https://pwpush.com/p.json',
         { 'password[payload]': 'mypassword', 'password[expire_after_days]': '2',
           'password[expire_after_views]': '10' }, 
           function(data) { console.log('Share this secret URL: https://pwpush.com/p/' + data.url_token) } )
</code></pre>

<p><%= _('See more explanation and examples in our') %> <a href="https://github.com/pglombardo/PasswordPusher/wiki/Password-API">Github Wiki</a>.</p>
